name: CancerTreatmentAgentsWhichMayCauseNeutropenia
title: Cancer Treatment Agents Which May Cause Neutropenia
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: This value set intends to identify cancer treatment agents which may cause neutropenia, which are taken orally or intravenously.),(Data Element Scope: This data element maps to the Medication category of the QDM.),(Inclusion Criteria: ALKYLATING AGENTS: bendamustine, chlorambucil, cyclophosphamide, ifosfamide, mechlorethamine, melphalan, carmustine, lomustine, carboplatin, cisplatin, busulfan, temozolomide
ANTIMETABOLITES: methotrexate, pemetrexed, pralatrexate, azacitidine, decitabine, cladribine, clofarabine, fludarabine, mercaptopurine, pentostatin, thioguanine, capecitabine, cytarabine, floxuridine, fluorouracil, gemcitabine
ANTITUMOR ANTIBIOTICS: daunorubicin, doxorubicin, epirubicin, idarubicin, mitoxantrone, actinomycin, mitomycin,
MITOTIC INHIBITORS: irinotecan, topotecan, etoposide, cabazitaxel, docetaxel, paclitaxel, vinblastine, vinorelbine, altretamine, dacarbazine, eribulin, hydroxyurea, procarbazine, teniposide, topotecan
TARGETED ANTICANCER DRUGS: dasatinib,
 pazopanib, ibritumomab, rituximab, tositumomab, bortezomib, romidepsin,
 alemtuzumab, gemtuzumab),(Exclusion Criteria: Codes not identified within the inclusion criteria.)
